{"lemma":"بَعِيدُو","slug":"بَعِيدُو","root":"ب.ع.د","root_slug":"ب-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ع-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَعِيد","root":"بعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":25},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","prep"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2874","n2875"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"far, remote, distant","examples":[{"text":"وَمَا هِيَ مِنَ الظَّالِمِينَ بِبَعِيدٍ","english":"And it is not far off from the wrongdoers."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"improbable","examples":[{"text":"أَإِذَا مِتْنَا وَكُنَّا تُرَابًا ذَٰلِكَ رَجْعٌ بَعِيدٌ","english":"When we have died and have become dust? That is a distant return."},{"text":"لَكِنَّ هَذَا بَعِيدٌ، لِأَنَّهُ لَوْ جَازَ هَذَا فِي هَذَا لَجَازَ مِثْلُهُ فِي جَمِيعِ القُرْآنِ، أَنْ يُجْعَلَ أَوَّلُ الآيَةِ فِي آخِرِهَا، وَآخِرُهَا فِي أَوَّلِهَا.","english":"Majdi Baslom"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"shortly after, soon after"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb بَعُدَ (baʕuda, “to be far”).\n\nDiminutive of بَعْد (baʕd)."},"ipa":["/ba.ʕiːd/","/bu.ʕaj.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2874","headword_ar":"بَعِيدٌ","root":"bEd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distant; remote; far; far off;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEaAdN","text_ar":"بُعَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEidN","text_ar":"بَاعِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K:) pl. (of the first, S, L)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEodaAnN","text_ar":"بُعْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and (of the first also, L, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEudN","text_ar":"بُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEaAdN","text_ar":"بِعَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and (of the first and second, L)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEadaA='u","text_ar":"بُعَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) and of the third, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEadN","text_ar":"بَعَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but this (which is also used as a sing. epithet, as will be shown in what follows,) is properly a quasi-pl. n.,] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdimN","text_ar":"خَادِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) As signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distant with respect to place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is correctly used alike as masc. and fem. and sing. and dual and pl.; (L, and TA in this art. and in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrb","text_ar":"قرب"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which latter see the authorities;) but not necessarily; like its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa baEiydN minoka","text_ar":"هِىَ بَعِيدٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is distant from thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is] as though you said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnuhaA baEiydN","text_ar":"مَكَانُهَا بَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"page_break","n":226},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota min~aA bibaEiydK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ مِنَّا بِبَعِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not distant from us"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anotumo min~aA bibaEiydK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتُمْ مِنَّا بِبَعِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye are not distant from us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~aA bibaEadK","text_ar":"مِنَّا بِبَعَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anotumu min~aA bibaEadK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتُمُ مِنَّا بِبَعَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) [But it receives, sometimes, the fem. form when used in this sense; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu baEiydFA minoka","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ بَعِيدًا مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydapN minoka","text_ar":"بَعِيدَةٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are phrases mentioned as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote in place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloof, from thee;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnFA","text_ar":"مَكَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHiyapF","text_ar":"نَاحِيَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like] being understood. (L.) You say also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozilN baEadN","text_ar":"مَنْزِلٌ بَعَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, place of alighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaH~a gayora baEiydK","text_ar":"تَنَحَّ غَيْرَ بَعِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayora baAEidK","text_ar":"غَيْرَ بَاعِدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayora baEadK","text_ar":"غَيْرَ بَعَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Retire thou not far;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou near:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [or] the second and third of these phrases mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retire thou not in an abject,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contemptible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"despicable, state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoTaliqo yaA fulaAnu gayora baAEidK","text_ar":"اِنْطَلِقْ يَا فُلَانُ غَيْرَ بَاعِدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Depart thou, O such a one, not far;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou not go away!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu mino","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydK","text_ar":"بَعِيدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, from afar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a mino","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydK","text_ar":"بَعِيدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came from afar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydN","text_ar":"بَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a desert and the like, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Far extending."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEodN baAEidN","text_ar":"بُعْدٌ بَاعِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A far distance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niy~apN baEiydapN","text_ar":"نِيَّةٌ بَعِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distant, far-reaching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far-aiming, intention, purpose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"design."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN baEiydu Alhim~api","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَعِيدُ الهِمَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is far-aiming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faraspiring, in purpose, desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ambition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa baEiydapu AlEahodi","text_ar":"هِىَ بَعِيدَةُ العَهْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"met, a long time ago"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: in this case, the fem. form, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", must be used. (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawolN baEiydN","text_ar":"قَوْلٌ بَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A saying far from being probable"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct; improbable; far-fetched; extraordinary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strange"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN baEiydN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ بَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An extraordinary thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, of which the like does not happen"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occur."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distant with respect to kindred"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which sense, the word receives the fem. form, [as well as the dual form, and pl. forms, like its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] by universal consent. (TA.) [Its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEadaA='u","text_ar":"بُعَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strangers, that are not relations."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino buEodaAni AlA^amiyri","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ بُعْدَانِ الاَمِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the distant dependents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subjects, of the governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prince"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA lamo takuno mino qurobaAni","text_ar":"اـِذَا لَمْ تَكُنْ مِنْ قُرْبَانِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amiyri fakuno mino buEodaAnihi","text_ar":"الاَمِيرِ فَكُنْ مِنْ بُعْدَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou be not of the particular companions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"familiars, of the governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prince, then be of his distant dependents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subjects"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e., be distant from him, that his evil may not affect thee. (AZ, A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu baEiydaAti","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ بَعِيدَاتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonK","text_ar":"بَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodN","text_ar":"بَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the latter half of the paragraph. ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEidN","text_ar":"بَاعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["L","K","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2875","headword_ar":"بُعَيْد","root":"bEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEayodaAt","text_ar":"بُعَيْدَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodu","text_ar":"بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}